other_tests.findings: Anti-AB42 peptide antibodies (513 pg per milliliter) and anti-Tau protein antibodies (905 pg per milliliter). Normal cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) pressures, cell counts, protein and glucose determinations, cytologic studies, and anti-MATA, antineuronal nuclear, and anti-Purkinje cell antibody studies.

Normal conduction velocities and distal motor latencies with low amplitude of the compound motor action potentials, needle electromyographic study showed fibrillations, positive sharp waves, and abundant fasciculations. Changes indicated lower motor neuron disease.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Fasciculations developed six weeks after discharge.
